d":false,"author_url":"https://www.youtube.com/@kylezaking","is_favorited":false,"_time_text":"16 years ago","timestamp":1272499200,"is_pinned":false},{"id":"UgxsQ1gja6zvLmS1hC14AaABAg","parent":"root","text":"I have no idea what a ritardando even is. I've never even heard the word before.\n\nYeah, I just slowed each file down progressively because the tempo does scale down there in the original tune. It also jumps up at the start of the 2nd file, and down again at the start of the 8th and onwards, hence so many files at the end.","like_count":0,"author_id":"UCuSVSeiwAeCg_z6Dn7-cPpQ","author":"@MediaMunkee","author_thumbnail":"https://yt3.ggpht.com/ytc/AIdro_ncYbSdSA9uPB_8WZdLESAE3cKNZsG94vToV-6BFN6rOmE=s88-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj","author_is_uploader":true,"author_is_verified":false,"author_url":"https://www.youtube.com/@MediaMunkee","is_favorited":false,"_time_text":"17 years ago","timestamp":1240963200,"is_pinned":false},{"id":"UgxgNpMBrURcW-ADk5J4AaABAg","parent":"root","text":"This is awesome. I was just wondering what was up with files 11, 12 and 13. Did you use lag to simulate a ritardando? If so, I think that's like the most awesome thing I've ever seen before. I would have never thought of it. Or maybe... did you just have each file at a slower tempo? That would make more sense now that I think about it. I've never thought of that either, but that's awesome too!","like_count":0,"author_id":"UCa9NGDVNQnkl-oCclyO_BBw","author":"@Gallahaut","author_thumbnail":"https://yt3.ggpht.com/ytc/AIdro_kyyuvsEZzPdAVfGGnR_-VC2Vifh2SytRkrSMIDoJNMwjU=s88-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj","author_is_uploader":false,"author_is_verified":false,"author_url":"https://www.youtube.com/@Gallahaut","is_favorited":false,"_time_text":"17 years ago","timestamp":1240963200,"is_pinned":false},{"id":"UgyxqCvkSPEiswz0sad4AaABAg","parent":"root","text":"You're right about getting instruments by ear: it's very painfulO_o.\r\n\r\nVery nice! Another song that I didn't know and now I love it.","like_count":